{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Generate Tests from Codebase",
  "description": "Scans the app's source code (Compose, SwiftUI, XML layouts), identifies screens, interactive elements, and user flows, then generates reusable YAML test scripts in e2e-tests/ folder with cross-platform support.",
  "version": "2",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Scan the mobile app source code in this workspace. Find all UI source files — look for: Kotlin Compose (*.kt with @Composable), SwiftUI (*.swift with View protocol/body), XML layouts (res/layout/*.xml), UIKit storyboards/xibs. Also scan AndroidManifest.xml, navigation graphs, build.gradle for app metadata. STEP 1 — DEEP SCAN & UNDERSTAND: Read through the ENTIRE codebase first. Identify all screens, activities, fragments, navigation flows, interactive elements, API calls, authentication logic, data models, custom views, and third-party SDKs. Understand the full app architecture BEFORE generating anything. STEP 2 — AUTO-GENERATE prompt/ FILES: Based on what you found, create the prompt/ folder and generate these files in order: a) prompt/00-prerequisites.md — App package name, main activity, login credentials needed (infer from auth logic), emulator setup notes (permissions to grant, settings to configure), test account info. b) prompt/01-testable-flows.md — List ALL flows that CAN be fully automated via UI automation. Group by module. Include recommended execution order based on dependencies (e.g., login first). For each flow: name, screens involved, why it's testable. c) prompt/02-untestable-flows.md — List ALL flows that CANNOT be automated. For each: name, reason (OTP required, real payment, camera/biometrics, server-side state, etc.), what would be needed to make it testable. Include handling rules: 'Do NOT generate test scripts for these flows. If encountered during execution, mark as Skip with reference to this file.' d) prompt/03-navigation-guide.md — How to navigate the app: entry points, screen transitions, tab structure, drawer/menu patterns, deep links if any. Common navigation patterns the agent should follow (e.g., 'always login first before testing authenticated screens'). e) prompt/04-known-issues.md — Workarounds for automation challenges found in code: custom views (MaterialCardView buttons → use coordinate tap), WebViews (can't inspect elements), animations (need waits), EditText that don't respond to ADB (use mobile_type_keys instead), any accessibility label gaps. STEP 3 — READ ALL prompt/*.md back as context for test script generation. STEP 4 — GENERATE TEST SCRIPTS: Only generate scripts for flows listed in prompt/01-testable-flows.md. Never generate scripts for flows in prompt/02-untestable-flows.md. For each testable flow: 1) Identify interactive elements with accessibility labels. 2) Generate test scripts with QUALITY OVER QUANTITY. PRIORITIZE critical user flows, error states, state transitions. AVOID redundant/trivial/overlapping tests. Each test UNIQUE, 2-3 high-value per feature, detailed steps, SPECIFIC expected results. 3) Save YAML in e2e-tests/ following generate-from-codebase steering schema. Order by flow from prompt/01-testable-flows.md. 4) Determine platform (Kotlin/XML → android; Swift → ios). STEP 5 — METADATA: Generate e2e-tests/coverage.yaml listing elements and coverage. Read e2e-tests/version.yaml — increment or set to 1. Output summary: screens found, prompt files generated, testable vs untestable flows count, test scripts generated."
  }
}